  "decisions": {
    "dualManifest": "YES. One component root (loom-nucleus/) carries sibling .codex-plugin/plugin.json and .claude-plugin/plugin.json over shared skills/ and hooks/. Canonical shared agents render as Vercel-shaped skill packages consumed by both Codex and Claude; legacy Claude agents/*.md role ports are superseded.",
    "writeBoth": "Write BOTH the marketplace catalog AND the loom-nucleus plugin distribution copy to a live home path through the strict-manual gate; canonical shared-agent packages are authored under repo nucleus/skills/{agent-name}/ and rendered to ~/.agents/plugins/loom-nucleus/skills/{agent-name}/.",
    "marketplaceRoot": "~/.agents/plugins (marketplace.json lives here; Codex auto-discovers it and reports the marketplace ROOT as $HOME)",
    "pluginSourceRoot": "~/.agents/plugins/loom-nucleus",
    "sourcePathReconciliation": "VERIFIED LIVE (LOO-15, codex-cli 0.142.0): Codex auto-discovers ~/.agents/plugins/marketplace.json with marketplace ROOT = $HOME and resolves source.path relative to that root, so source.path is './.agents/plugins/loom-nucleus' (./-prefixed, inside the $HOME root), NOT './loom-nucleus'. Install with `codex plugin add loom-nucleus@loom-nucleus-plugins` (the verb is `add`, not `install`); no `marketplace add` is needed (auto-discovered). policy.installation=AVAILABLE, authentication=ON_INSTALL, category=Productivity all parse and install+enable cleanly.",
    "claudeMarketplace": "Repo-scoped .claude-plugin/marketplace.json is rendered to distributions/loom-nucleus/.claude-plugin/marketplace.json (also read by Codex as a legacy-compatible repo marketplace) and is rendered + gated + reported, never written to HOME.",
    "versionPinning": "Pin an explicit plugin version (0.1.0) rather than relying on commit-SHA versioning (resolved open question 7).",
    "stopHookTrust": "Ship the Stop verifier dormant. Document a one-time manual /hooks trust step; AFK auto-arming of the verifier is deferred (resolved open questions 8: option (a)).",
    "stopHookSemantics": "The Stop verifier reports (non-zero exit + structured reason) and does not block turn completion (design 4.3 default).",
    "neverWrite": [
      "~/.codex/plugins/cache/",
      "~/.claude/plugins/cache/",
      "~/.claude/plugins/data/",
      "~/.codex/auth.json",
      "~/.claude/settings.local.json"
    ],
    "canonicalSharedAgentPackages": "LOO-105 makes nucleus/skills/{agent-name}/ the canonical repo-local Vercel-shaped shared-agent package source: AGENTS.md, SKILL.md, references/*, and exemplars/* per agent. The plugin bridge derives shared-agent package candidates directly from that source at render/validation time; committed byte-copy plugin package output is intentionally absent."
  },
